column1:
1. Try your best to segment each domain into its component words (there are multiple "correct" segmentations)
2. The Segmentation column contains the domain names with the ".com" removed.
3. To segment a domain, place "|" characters in between the words in the Segmentation column. Do not place a "|" at the beginning of the first word or
the end of the last word
4. In the English? (Yes/No) column, please indicate whether you believe that the domain name consists of English words.
5. The sample of domain names has been filtered using a blacklist of offensive terms, but some offensive domain names may have been missed by the filter. 
If you encounter any offensive domain names, please delete the corresponding row.

If you have any questions, please email: leandr@oregonstate.edu

Thank you for your time!

1. When 2 words share a substring, place the "|" at the end of the first word.
2. Treat strings of random characters as a single word.
3. Remove delimiters dashes and underscores.
4. "Made-up" words (eg. brand names) should be treated as a single word. 
5. Segment compound words into their component words.
